<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: lightblue;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        .styled-paragraph {
            color: blue;
            font-size: 16px;
        }
        .background-color {
            background-color: blue; /* This will set the background color */
            color: white; /* Adjust text color for better visibility */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>It's Rima again. I'm a teenager, so it's bad.</h1>
    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
    <p class="styled-paragraph">This is a styled paragraph.</p>
    <p>See? I changed the color too ... wait, I'm acting like Doraaaaa. Ugh.</p>
    <p><b><u>Never mind, I'll try to write something nicer later.</u></b></p>
    <p class="background-color">And the background is refreshing.</p>
    <table>
        <!-- Add your table content here -->
    </table>
</body>
</html>